Reply with a single fenced block — nothing else, no narration:

```plan
{"status":"ok","body":{"next_wave":{"label":"<kebab-case-label>","subagents":[{"name":"<short-name>","role":"<role-from-sub_agents>","task":"<one-paragraph brief>"}]},"roadmap":["<later-wave-label>","..."],"rationale":"<why this wave next>"}}
```

The triple-backticks and the word `plan` are mandatory; the JSON
inside must parse. Required keys:
- `status` — `"ok"` for a normal plan; `"error"` with a `reason`
  field to bail.
- `body.next_wave` — the wave to run next, OR `null` to signal that
  the mission is complete and synthesis should run. When set, must
  carry `label` (kebab-case, unique per mission) and one or more
  `subagents` (each with `name`, `role`, `task`).
- `body.roadmap` — array of anticipated future wave labels (may be
  empty). Hint only; the runtime does not auto-run them.
- `body.rationale` — one paragraph explaining why this is the next
  wave.

Optional keys: `memory_summary` (carried into the next planner's
plan_context), `body.next_wave.subagents[*].depends_on` (array of
handoff refs from earlier waves), `body.next_wave.subagents[*].inputs`
(structured JSON the worker receives alongside its task).
